-- Moody’s Cuts Rating for Slovenia’s NLB State-Backed Bonds
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-02-16T14:01:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/moody-s-cuts-rating-for-slovenia-s-nlb-state-backed-bonds.html
Moody’s Investors Service cut the
rating of Slovenia’s Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d. state-backed
bonds to A2 from A1 following the cut on Slovenia’s sovereign
rating. The outlook is negative.  NLB, as the bank is known, commented in the statement to
the Ljubljana stock exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  